faq:
  - q: "What does the discovery call cost?"
    a: "Nothing. The 30-minute discovery call is complimentary, there&rsquo;s no hourly billing, and the written fixed-fee scope that follows is non-binding. Every engagement is priced from the canonical figures published on our <a href=\"/pricing/\">pricing page</a> &mdash; the scope you receive cites them."
  - q: "Will I get a sales pitch on the call?"
    a: "No. A Certified ProAdvisor reviews where your books are and recommends the right engagement &mdash; or none, if that&rsquo;s the honest answer. There&rsquo;s no commission for steering you anywhere, no follow-up sales sequence, and the call ends with a clear next step you&rsquo;re free to ignore."
  - q: "What if TechBrot isn&rsquo;t the right fit for my situation?"
    a: "We&rsquo;ll say so on the call and point you toward what does fit &mdash; including firms outside TechBrot when that&rsquo;s the honest answer. The discovery call is complimentary either way, and you keep everything you learned from it."
  - q: "Do you only work with businesses already on QuickBooks?"
    a: "No. If you&rsquo;re on Xero, Wave, other software, or spreadsheets, the discovery call covers whether a <a href=\"/quickbooks/migration/\">migration</a> or a fresh <a href=\"/quickbooks/setup/\">QuickBooks setup</a> makes sense &mdash; and if staying put is the right answer, we&rsquo;ll tell you that. New businesses with no accounting infrastructure yet are a regular starting point."
  - q: "How does pricing work after the discovery call?"
    a: "You get a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days of the call. It binds us to the fee and the deliverables; it doesn&rsquo;t bind you. If genuinely new in-scope work emerges mid-engagement, we re-quote in writing before any of it happens &mdash; no scope creep, no hourly upcharges. Canonical figures live on the <a href=\"/pricing/\">pricing page</a>."
  - q: "Will I end up on a marketing list if I submit the form?"
    a: "No. Your details are used only to respond to this request &mdash; no marketing list, no sales follow-up sequence. The <a href=\"/legal/privacy-policy/\">privacy policy</a> covers exactly what happens to the information in the brief."
  - q: "My situation is urgent — can I skip the form?"
    a: "Yes. Call <a href=\"tel:+18777515575\" data-tb-event=\"phone_click\">(877) 751-5575</a>, Mon&ndash;Fri 9&nbsp;AM&ndash;6&nbsp;PM ET &mdash; a ProAdvisor answers during business hours. Or book directly on <a href=\"https://calendly.com/techbrot/discovery\" rel=\"noopener\">our calendar</a> without filling the form. Same operator, same outcome; the form just gets us the details before the call."
